The TrkA/B/C inhibitory activities of the designed molecules were preliminarily screened by utilizing fluorescence resonance energy transfer (FRET)-based Z′-Lyte kinase assays [41]. The cellular growth inhibition was further determined against a panel of BaF3 cells stably transformed with TrkA/B/C, respectively, for the representative compounds with promising kinase inhibitory potencies. FDA approved drug 1 was included as a positive reference compound to exhibit 2.9, 2.3 and 1.7 nM IC50 values in kinase assays, and suppressed the proliferation of BaF3 cells harboring TrkA/B/C with IC50 values of 0.016, 0.040 and 0.013 μM, respectively (Table 1
                      and Table 2
                     ). Encouragingly, our first designed compound 7a displayed comparable kinase inhibitory potencies with that of drug 1 with IC50 values of 7.6, 1.3 and 1.9 nM against TrkA, TrkB and TrkC (Table 1), respectively, providing a promising lead compound for further structural optimization.
